cts and the most abject ones, in a world where it seems anyone might do anything, from the beautiful to the horrendous.The Persistence of Violence draws on those contradictions and paradoxes to look at how violence-and resistance to it-characterize Colombian popular culture, from football to soap opera to journalism to tourism to the environment.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Mai 2021) 0aPopular culturezColumbia. 0aViolence in popular culturezColombia. 0aViolencezColombia. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / General.2bisacsh1 aArroyave, Jesús, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBarrios, Marta Milena, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBarrios, Marta Milena.1 aCabrera, Jesús Arroyave.1 aDuque, Anamaria Tamayo.1 aFajardo, Alfredo Sabbagh.1 aLucia Sorzano, Olga, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSabbagh Fajardo, Alfredo, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSorzano, Olga Lucia.1 aTamayo-Duque, Anamaria, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020 Englishz978311070471608iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020z9783110704518oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Social Sciences 2020 Englishz978311070472308iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Sociology, Education, Psychology 2020z9783110704549oZDB-23-SEW08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertRUP eBook-Package Frontlist 2020z978311069033040uhttps://doi.org/10.36019/9781978817555zCo-access DOI >> click Walter de Gruyter40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781978817555423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9781978817555.jpg  a978-3